The paper deals with efficient data structures and algorithms for manipulating matrices, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of hashing and queuing theory in the paper suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with numerical linear algebra, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of random matrices and probability theory suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
